aa(lp73
VLet me tell you a story.
p74
aVIt's about a woman called Justine Sacco.
p75
aVShe was a PR woman from New York with 170 Twitter followers,
p76
aVand she'd Tweet little acerbic jokes to them,
p77
aVlike this one on a plane from New York to London:
p78
aV[Weird German Dude: You're in first class. It's 2014. Get some deodorant."
p79
aV-Inner monologue as inhale BO. Thank god for pharmaceuticals.]
p80
aVSo Justine chuckled to herself, and pressed send, and got no replies,
p81
aVand felt that sad feeling that we all feel
p82
aVwhen the Internet doesn't congratulate us for being funny.
p83
aV(Laughter)
p84
aVBlack silence when the Internet doesn't talk back.
p85
aVAnd then she got to Heathrow, and she had a little time to spare
p86
aVbefore her final leg, so she thought up another funny little acerbic joke:
p87
aa(lp88
V[Going to Africa. Hope I don't get AIDS. Just kidding. I'm white!]
p89
aa(lp90
VAnd she chuckled to herself, pressed send, got on the plane, got no replies,
p91
aVturned off her phone, fell asleep,
p92
aVwoke up 11 hours later,
p93
aVturned on her phone while the plane was taxiing on the runway,
p94
aVand straightaway there was a message from somebody
p95
aVthat she hadn't spoken to since high school,
p96
aVthat said, "I am so sorry to see what's happening to you."
p97
aVAnd then another message from a best friend,
p98
aV"You need to call me right now.
p99
aVYou are the worldwide number one trending topic on Twitter."
p100
aV(Laughter)
